Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.32,0:00:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,today, rather than us just talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.55,0:00:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted you to really watch this scene, so we just had you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.27,0:00:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for sharing so many of your thoughts in the comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.84,0:00:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on this story, we'd like to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,how we approached our performances as actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.80,0:00:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep in mind that these are just our personal thoughts on what we focused on while acting,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.91,0:00:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so please keep that in mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.48,0:00:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,...as you listen. First, regarding Ena, for this Episode 8—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.52,0:01:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,well, not just Episode 8, but taking the previous story into account too—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.03,0:01:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when I tried to put myself in Ena's shoes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.75,0:01:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and think about things, I really couldn't find a "correct" answer at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered how she would actually feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.23,0:01:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or how she would act. I thought about it over and over, staring at the script from Ena's perspective until...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.03,0:01:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...the final
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.95,0:01:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Episode 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.59,0:01:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I got swept up in the atmosphere, and it was a bit...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how should I put it... I was on the verge of tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.11,0:01:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally, I just felt like I was going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.08,0:01:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,well, the tears were just overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.75,0:02:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There were detailed instructions like, "Cry here," or "Sniffle here."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.19,0:02:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So based on that, I first thought about how to play Ena as she cries here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.88,0:02:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and how I should approach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.91,0:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When I thought about it, I really wanted to tell Mizuki, "You're fine just the way you are,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.84,0:02:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and "You're important to me." I was planning my performance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.79,0:02:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with that single-minded focus in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.03,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to act with my own honest feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but when I actually went to the recording session,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.96,0:02:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,after they heard my first take, the director told me they wanted a "catfight."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.19,0:02:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.40,0:02:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When they said they wanted to see a catfight between Mizuki and Ena, I asked, "So I don't have to cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.24,0:02:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.84,0:02:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fight with them?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.84,0:02:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I started wondering what kind of Ena would do that, and it suddenly hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.79,0:02:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ena even says, "I haven't changed,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.63,0:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,right there in the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.96,0:03:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My original plan and the stage directions were both very lovely,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.68,0:03:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but that came from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.19,0:03:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,caring about Mizuki so much that I was being overly considerate. I felt like that wasn't right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.68,0:03:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that if it were Ena,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,she would do things differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.84,0:03:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, those feelings of caring are very important,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.63,0:03:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but because she cares, she should be able to clash with them and ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.63,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why don't you understand?" I realized that having their usual fight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.91,0:03:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually the important part.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.16,0:03:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I'm not Ena myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.12,0:03:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at it from the outside makes it seem like this grand ordeal—and the problem itself is something only Mizuki can truly understand—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.40,0:03:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,For the two of them—and for Ena—it was probably just a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.51,0:04:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just my opinion, but even though we made it out to be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.24,0:04:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a huge deal from an outsider's perspective...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.47,0:04:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,...I interpreted it as the first time these two finally clashed with someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.75,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kept that in mind while performing the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually worried because I couldn't quite connect
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.63,0:04:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the angry Ena I'd imagined with the illustration...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.27,0:04:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...but it turned out so wonderful that I'm just relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.80,0:04:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.48,0:04:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.83,0:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Episode 8 was like that, but since we're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.24,0:04:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd also like to hear about the banter with Mizuki. Do we have time for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.12,0:04:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,schedule-wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.07,0:04:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, from Mizuki's perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you really can't miss Episode 8 in either case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.71,0:05:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In the previous Episode 8, Ena was often at a loss for words,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so for me, that was really all there was to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.48,0:05:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.48,0:05:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizuki-{\i1}chan{\i0}, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,To talk about it a bit... for the previous event, "Where Shall This Path Lead?", and this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually asked to record standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.83,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hesitating until the very last minute, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when it comes to voice acting,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the type who feels I need to really "act" with my voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.83,0:05:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,so standing up makes it feel more like being on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.51,0:05:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought about it, and well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.92,0:05:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're crying, your legs naturally lose their strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to really focus on the voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.24,0:05:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it might be better to sit down while recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.31,0:06:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For Episode 8 of the previous event, "The Path to the Curved Melody"...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.48,0:06:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,my initial plan was that even while crying,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.12,0:06:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they would still be able to speak clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.31,0:06:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I got direction saying, "I want you to cry more," so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably did about three or four more takes after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.63,0:06:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I recorded both that time and this time
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,without hearing Minori-chan's lines, so I heard their conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.04,0:06:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time as all of you. I was like, "Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so this is how the final scene turned out!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And well,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.88,0:06:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because of that, I feel like I was able to give it my absolute all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.15,0:06:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We see each other quite often even if we don't meet during recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.15,0:06:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're always asking each other, "How did you record that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.19,0:06:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or "What kind of direction did you get?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We talk about that all the time. And, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.24,0:06:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just a small request for the staff, but
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.12,0:06:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we were saying how wonderful it would be if we could record together in the same studio one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:06:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The ProSeka staff
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really respect the actors' performances, so as
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizuki and Ena grow,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they might run into another big wall again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But they might take action to save someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.15,0:07:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I hope that next time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.75,0:07:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we can have a back-and-forth in a wonderful scene like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And even without that, we're kind of like, "We really nailed it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.31,0:07:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Or rather, "Yay!" in a way, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.71,0:07:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we've talked quite a bit,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.19,0:07:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's almost time, so let's all watch
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.75,0:07:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the AfterLive together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.36,0:07:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Private...
